  "prompt": "What would be the quadratic equation for the roots 2+\u221a2 and 2-\u221a2?",
  "response": "To find the quadratic equation for the given roots, we can use the fact that a quadratic equation can be written as:\n\nx\u00b2 - (sum of the roots)x + (product of the roots) = 0\n\nGiven the roots: 2+\u221a2 and 2-\u221a2\n\nStep 1: Calculate the sum of the roots\n(2+\u221a2) + (2-\u221a2) = 2 + 2 + \u221a2 - \u221a2 = 4\n\nStep 2: Calculate the product of the roots\n(2+\u221a2) * (2-\u221a2) = (2)\u00b2 - (\u221a2)\u00b2 = 4 - 2 = 2\n\nNow, we can write the quadratic equation as:\n\nx\u00b2 - (sum of the roots)x + (product of the roots) = 0\nx\u00b2 - 4x + 2 = 0\n\nSo, the quadratic equation for the roots 2+\u221a2 and 2-\u221a2 is x\u00b2 - 4x + 2 = 0.",
